✦ I have implemented the corner actions feature.

  I created a new module modules/CornerActions.qml that monitors the four corners of every screen. It reads its configuration from ~/.config/caelestia/shell.json. I also integrated this module into your
  main shell.qml.

  Configuration
  To use this feature, add a corners section to your ~/.config/caelestia/shell.json file. Here is an example configuration:

   1 {
   2   "corners": {
   3     "topLeft": { "action": "dashboard", "delay": 250 },
   4     "topRight": { "action": "launcher", "delay": 250 },
   5     "bottomLeft": { "action": "session", "delay": 250 },
   6     "bottomRight": { "action": "command: kitty", "delay": 500 }
   7   }
   8 }

  Supported Actions:
   - dashboard: Toggle the dashboard.
   - launcher: Toggle the app launcher.
   - session: Toggle the session menu.
   - sidebar: Toggle the sidebar.
   - utilities: Toggle the utilities drawer.
   - osd: Toggle the on-screen display.
   - command: <your command>: Execute a custom shell command (e.g., command: kitty or command: notify-send "Corner triggered").

  The delay is in milliseconds and defaults to 250ms if not specified. The actions are triggered relative to the screen where the mouse is located.
