✦ I have addressed the issues with the configuration by moving the corner settings to a dedicated singleton that uses PersistentProperties. This resolves the "unknown option" warning and prevents the
  configuration from being cleared when the shell reloads. I also added a new settings pane in the Control Center to make it easy to configure the actions.

  Summary of Changes
   1. Created services/CornerSettings.qml: A new singleton that stores the configuration for all four corners. It uses PersistentProperties, which automatically handles saving and loading to a dedicated
      file, avoiding conflicts with shell.json.
   2. Updated modules/CornerActions.qml: Modified to use the new CornerSettings singleton instead of reading shell.json directly.
   3. Added modules/controlcenter/corners/CornersPane.qml: A new settings page in the Control Center where you can easily set actions and delays for each corner.
   4. Registered the new pane: Updated modules/controlcenter/PaneRegistry.qml to include the "Corners" settings page.

  How to use
   1. Open the Control Center.
   2. Navigate to the new Corners tab (look for the corner icon).
   3. Set your desired actions (e.g., dashboard, launcher, or command: kitty) and delays for each corner.
   4. The settings are saved automatically and will persist across shell reloads.

  This approach is much cleaner and integrates better with the existing system's architecture.


